Fourth, the numinous diagrams, which depict the marks of excellence;
Fifth, the genealogical records, which trace the transmission of the Dao through the ages;
Sixth, the precepts and disciplines, which guard against transgressions and restrain evil;
Seventh, the ritual decorum, which establishes the norms of conduct in the academies;
Eighth, the methods and practices, which regulate the progress of cultivation;
Ninth, the arts and calculations, which conceal the luminous and honor the form;
Tenth, the records and biographies, which transmit teachings to learners;
Eleventh, the hymns and eulogies, which sing of the sagely virtue;
Twelfth, the memorials and petitions, which present prayers and supplications.

The Three Caverns thoroughly penetrate responsive transformation, verifying the three vehicles. The accumulation of merit and verification of fruition also differ. According to the height of merit, one ascends to the various heavens. The karmic rewards of the heavens are attested by the sutras’ explanations. The thirty-six sections verify the ranks of rebirth in the heavens. The thirty-six heavens correspond to the ranks cultivated through the sutras. By ascending, one verifies the Dao-fruit. Because there is the arising of cultivation, liberation has its conditions, and the natural true nature is thus.

The Yellow Thearch bowed twice and again inquired: "The thirty-six sections correspond to three ranks of conditions; the thirty-six heavens correspond to the ranks cultivated through the sutras. The sutras verify the heavenly ranks, and by relying on the sutras, one is reborn in heaven. The three ranks respond to the sutras. Yet the common people are benighted and weak, unaware of the source of the Dao. Do they verify the ranks and achieve penetration?"

The Lord of Nurturance replied: "The scriptural methods of the Three Caverns are the gateways of the Heavenly Worthy. Responsive transformation and life’s arising all proceed from the establishment of marks. The body’s radiance illumines brilliantly, shining through the Grand Void. The realms of heaven and humanity all receive and plant these. The Three Treasures respond to images; the Nine Thearchs assist in forming them. Wondrous existence pervades and nourishes, first giving rise to the spirit’s awareness. When the spirit is clear and wisdom bright, the will mirrors and wisdom shines. When qi is turbid and the spirit dull, darkness and obscurity arise. When the body harmonizes with the Great Dao, the realm’s penetration is mysterious. In tranquil contemplation, the body’s spirits merge with the Three Clarities. The Eight Effulgences uphold and elevate, settling the cloud chariot’s course. The Nine Heavens assist in forming, subtly ascending to the pure realm. The thirty-six sections illumine your body; the thirty-six heavens’ contemplation follows the heart’s mastery. Listen carefully to my words, and I will explain it to you."

The Lord of Tranquility addressed the Yellow Thearch: "The utmost Dao is without image, without form or name. From its root, it descends in traces, gradually manifesting the Three Bodies. From the arising of the Three Bodies, the Three Caverns unfold. The Three Realms and Three Worlds reveal the distinctions between the ordinary and the sagely. The Nine Heavens and Nine Persons respond to images and penetrate connections. The Three Treasures gradually and suddenly [transmit]; the Three Vehicles receive life. All arise from the Dharma-body, the body’s radiance and marks of excellence. The Three Bodies’ marks of excellence manifest the realm’s forms. Heavenly and human beings respond and transform, together nourishing and turning toward images. All plant their spirits from the marks of excellence, above receiving the mysterious essence, first accomplishing wondrous function.

The first is the Dharma-body, profoundly penetrating the subtle and obscure. The true and wondrous wisdom is pure and unimpeded. Above, it manifests the Dharma-body’s thirty-six gates, which unfold the Three Caverns’ thirty-six marks. Above and below correspond, forming seventy-two marks.

The second is the Response-body, which responds to the body and manifests images. The Three Realms and Three Worlds are perfectly luminous above and below. Descending qi gives rise to the spirit, forming numinous awareness. Immeasurable merits and virtues fully equip humans and heavens. Responding to karmic conditions, one verifies dwellings according to merit. Above, it manifests the Three Realms’ thirty-six heavens; below, it responds to the Three Worlds’ thirty-six Thearchs. Above and below penetrate and respond, forming seventy-two marks.

The third is the Transformation-body, which opens and transforms human spirits. All contain the Three Caverns; the nine qi give rise to life. Imitating heaven and earth, they unite to form awareness and numinosity. Internally, it manifests the Transformation-body’s thirty-six marks; externally, it displays the thirty-six marks of living humans. Internally and externally correspond, forming seventy-two marks.

The thirty-six sections are the source without marks. From principle, words are entrusted to weigh its pattern. Responding to the arising of realms, merits fill the ten directions. Returning to the root and reverting to the origin establishes the ranks of ascent. Verifying fruition and advancing in position, one transcends to the Great Network. Comprehending the Great Dao, one enters true actuality. Perfectly fulfilling purity and clarity, beneficence spreads to the black-haired people. Skillfully opening expedient means, it demonstrates conditioned dharmas. Penetrating life’s wondrous function, it gives rise to awareness. Myriad transformations respond to conditions; the one mark is empty and tranquil."

The Lord of Tranquility addressed the Yellow Thearch: "The profound and quiescent Dharma-body gives rise to the empty and cavernous. Within the empty and cavernous, the Grand Source arises. From the Grand Source’s transformation, the three qi are born. The upper qi is called *Beginning*; the middle qi is called *Origin*; the lower qi is called *Mysterious*. The *Mysterious* qi gives rise to what issues from *Origin*; the *Origin* qi gives rise to what issues from *Beginning*. This qi’s root is the ancestral lord of images, hence it is called the *Mysterious-Origin-Beginning* qi.

The *Mysterious-Origin-Beginning* qi is the mysterious root of the Three Realms. Above, it responds to the Three Realms, establishing the Three Worthies. In the middle, it gives rise to the Three Worlds, the Three Vehicles receiving and guiding. Together, they form the Three Origins, giving rise to the Three Offices of humans. Thus, these three qi bestow ranks and give life. The three give rise to the myriad existences, the root source and original beginning."

The Lord of Tranquility addressed the Yellow Thearch: "Within the Three Clarities’ heavens, the *Mysterious-Origin-Beginning* qi combines three with five, transforming into the Eight Effulgent Spirits. Each gives rise to the eight directions, forming the Twenty-Four Thearchs. Above, they become the Three Clarities’ Twenty-Four Palaces, the Purple Void’s immortal precincts. Descending, they become the Four Brahmās. The four eights transform and give rise to the Three Worlds’ Twenty-Four Palaces, universally forming one heaven’s twenty-four qi, which internally give rise to the human body’s twenty-four constituents. Thus, these Three Origins, Three Sections, Eight Effulgences, and Twenty-Four Thearchs—each Thearch has three origins, each origin has five spirits, combining to form three hundred sixty spirits. The six sixes’ ranked lineages combine qi to give rise to spirits. Above, they form the Three Clarities’ sixty-four Brahmā qi. Two sixes combine, forming thirty-two, which descend to give rise to the Three Worlds’ thirty-two heavens, universally forming one heaven’s thirty-two Thearchs. The twenty-eight lodges, the jade armillary sphere, thus give rise to one heaven’s three hundred sixty days, one month’s three hundred sixty hours, one earth’s three hundred sixty famous mountains, and one human body’s three hundred sixty bones."

The Lord of Tranquility addressed the Yellow Thearch: "The *Mysterious-Origin-Beginning* qi combines to give rise to the nine qi, hence forming the Nine Thearchs. Above, they become the Nine Heavens; in the middle, they give rise to the Nine Heavens; below, they become the Nine Earths. The Nine Sages of the various heavens all fully possess form and spirit. They give rise to the nine apertures of humans, who receive the Dao and establish life."

The Fourth Section on the Manifestation of the Dharmakāya of the Supreme Dao and the Primordial Establishment of Marks and Characteristics

At that time, the Yellow Emperor ascended Cloud Terrace Mountain, paid homage to Lord Ning, and inquired about the Three Caverns and their three grades of liberation, as well as the reception of heaven and humanity. He further asked about the realms through which the Three Treasures communicate life, and how these realms connect to the generation of heaven and humanity, how humanity connects to the generation of the Dao, how generation connects to the essence of the Dao, and how the Dao connects to the boundless. All forms and spirits are universally endowed; the Supreme Dao is impartial—how then does its transformative response differ?

Lord Ning replied to the Yellow Emperor: The Three Caverns and Nine Emperors, the Nine Celestial Gates of Life, and the sacred ranks of immortals and perfected beings each possess nine grades and twenty-seven ranks. The graded ranks of the Three Caverns, from mortal to immortal, comprise eighty-one levels, originally established as the Three Vehicles to serve as graded ranks due to the confusion and darkness within the Three Realms.

The Jade Emperor of the Supreme Dao, whose merit pervades the ten directions, established the Three Treasures. The Three Honored Ones differ in manifestation, each displaying a distinct trikāya. Thus, during the Dragon Han kalpa, responding to the sacred teaching, he was titled the Heavenly Worthy of the Formless; during the Crimson Brightness kalpa, responding to the true teaching, he was titled the Heavenly Worthy of the Unenlightened; and during the Supreme August kalpa, responding to the immortal teaching, he was titled the Heavenly Worthy of Primordial Beginning.

The Three Treasures respond to teachings, the Three Vehicles differ in grade, and the responsive transformation bodies vary in their original and manifested traces. In the primordial Dragon Han kalpa, within the Bright Rosy Clouds Observatory of the Great Luo Heaven, he unfolded the Three Caverns and thirty-six sections, each corresponding to a realm of generation, with thirty-six heavens therein. He expounded the Ten Titles of the Primordial Chaos of Heaven. The mysterious primal qi transformed into the mysterious image, radiant with luminous brilliance, layered in ninefold splendor, and perfectly round in eightfold clarity. From this arose the marks and characteristics, the realms of generation, and the transformation of bodies into humanity. The karmic retribution of heaven and humanity, whether mortal or sage, differs. The trikāya and their marks vary in superior, middle, and inferior grades. The establishment of human spirits all relies upon the transformed body.

Lord Ning told the Yellow Emperor: In the primordial kalpa, the Jade Emperor of the Supreme Dao, the Heavenly Worthy of the Formless, within the Bright Rosy Clouds Observatory of the Great Luo Heaven, expounded the Ten Titles of the Three Caverns’ responsive generation. He spread the Nine Emperors to establish the Nine Heavens, with the sacred ranks of immortals and perfected beings serving as the mysterious ford of the Three Treasures, and the twenty-seven ranks as the cultivation grades of the realms. The thirty-six sections, above, form the mysterious root of the Three Realms, and below, serve as the responsive abodes of the Three Realms and thirty-six heavens. The seventy-two marks manifest the forms of the realms; the eighty-one excellences are the origin of the generation of heaven and humanity. Their ebb and flow, their transformations, pervade the great chiliocosm. Through exhalation and inhalation, they respond with bodies, generating five hundred million beings. The boundless Three Realms stretch infinitely, their realms connecting to the spirit, universally endowed above and below. In each kalpa, they manifest differently, their names and titles varying. Across successive kalpas, their transformation bodies and honored names differ.

The first title is *Yuan* (Source), the source and origin;
The second is *Hun* (Mixed), undifferentiated and inseparable;
The third is *Dun* (Chaotic), vast and uncarved;
The fourth is *Ming* (Abysmal), profound and obscure;
The fifth is *Xing* (Vast), boundless and infinite;
The sixth is *Meng* (Misty), like fine mist;
The seventh is *Hong* (Surging), like billowing waves;
The eighth is *Shi* (Beginning), where the primal qi congeals in the Great Luo;
The ninth is *Yuan* (Primordial), the eldest of virtues;
The tenth is *Xuan* (Mysterious), lord of the upper heavens.

Mysterious beyond the mysterious, the Heavenly Lord, addressed as "Your Majesty," is the supreme origin of generation. Thus, the Heavenly Worthy of the Nameless, from the eighth title *Shi* (Beginning Qi) of the Great Luo, first generated the Jade Clarity, responding with the sacred teaching of the Great Cavern Dharma Gate. Next, from the ninth title *Yuan* (Primordial Qi) of the Jade Clarity, descended the Supreme Clarity, responding with the true teaching of the Cavern Mystery Dharma Gate. Then, from the tenth title *Xuan* (Mysterious Qi) of the Supreme Clarity, descended the Grand Clarity, responding with the immortal teaching of the Cavern Spirit Dharma Gate.

Furthermore, the Three Realms descend from the Three Realms above. The realms respond to one another, the Three Vehicles differ in grade, and the Three Realms guide accordingly, each distinct. The Sacred Realm of Jade Clarity connects below to the Formless Realm; the True Realm of Supreme Clarity connects below to the Form Realm; the Immortal Realm of Grand Clarity connects below to the Desire Realm.

Moreover, the Three Caverns generate human spirits, connecting heaven and humanity, harmonizing the nine portals. The Sacred Realm of Jade Clarity generates the upper one of humanity, the Upper Palace of Mud Pill; the True Realm of Supreme Clarity generates the middle one of humanity, the Crimson Palace of the Perfected; the Immortal Realm of Grand Clarity generates the lower one of humanity, the Yellow Court Immortal Palace. Thus, the Primordial King of the Yellow Court below humanity serves as the life-spirit, the master of breath and destiny.

The Dao of immortals governs life, and through life, cultivation is practiced. The word "immortal" (*xian*) means "to ascend" (*qian*); ascending to the Grand Clarity is immortality. Ascending from immortality to perfection enters the Supreme Clarity; ascending from perfection to sageliness enters the Jade Clarity; ascending from sageliness to the Dao enters the Great Luo. The realm of the Supreme Dao is vast, principle congealed in stillness.

*Upper Clarity’s Most High Scripture of Opening Heaven and Mounting the Dragon, Scroll Three*

The Fifth Section on the Primordial Establishment of the Thirty-Six Marks of the Three Caverns as Responded and Expounded by the Heavenly Worthy of Primordial Beginning

At that time, the Yellow Emperor, having received and bowed to Lord Ning’s exposition of the Heavenly Worthy’s transformative affairs, further inquired about the origin of the generation of heaven. The mysterious primal qi, the mysterious root of the Three Realms, descends to generate the Three Realms, universally endowing all phenomena. The Ten Titles of the Heavenly Worthy, the origin of the generation of the Three Caverns, the Three Realms and Three Realms above, all universally respond to this influence. The transformative descent of Primordial Beginning responds with marks to complete heaven—since heaven has generation, where lies the gateway of marks?

Lord Ning replied to the Yellow Emperor: In the past, I received the Heavenly Worthy’s decree in the primordial realm of generation within the Great Luo Heaven, unfolding the transformation of forms and spirits. Thus, the Heavenly Emperor was established, the life-essence constructed, and for all great sages, the *Most High Scripture of Opening Heaven* was expounded, with seventy-two marks and three kinds of responsive bodies, eighty-one excellences. Three degrees of transformed bodies descend from origin to trace, gradually manifesting activity. Thus, the dharmakāya is revealed, followed by the sambhogakāya, and then the nirmāṇakāya.

The realms of generation universally endow the responsive bodies. All heavenly and human beings respond to the function of generation, first forming spiritual consciousness and thus possessing the knowing spirit. The mysterious primal qi, the original source of the Three Caverns, the thirty-six sections, and the graded ranks of the realms—within the Jade Capital’s Mysterious Terrace, the Three Caverns respond and complete. Within the Purple Tenuity’s Golden Palace, the nine qi universally establish.

Thus the Dharma-body is revealed to manifest the celestial countenance, its responsive transformations universally pervading the mundane, wherein humans and heavens attain their abodes. The wondrous root of the Three Caverns establishes the radiance of the body, while the realms project form, and responsive conditions arise accordingly.

Unobstructed wondrous eloquence is called the sagely perfected; none surpass the exalted, for this is the form-body. Therefore, the nine transformations are displayed, the ninefold unity shaping form, the four nines universally pervading, comprising thirty-six grades. The thirty-six marks correspond to the three degrees of responsive bodies, liberation from the dust of clamor being the true and ultimate reality.

Wondrous and unobstructed, it responds as the Supreme Unity;
Radiant and unsurpassed, it responds as the August Unity;
Lord of the hundred spirits and sagely ancestor, it responds as the Imperial Unity;
Pure and serene, it responds as the True Unity;
Foremost of the ten thousand virtues, it responds as the Primal Unity;
True sovereign of yin, it responds as the Celestial Unity;
Vacuously pervading and unobstructed, it responds as the Mysterious Unity;
Great lord of longevity, it responds as the Grand Unity;
Dharma-king of the covenant’s majesty, it responds as the Orthodox Unity.

Within these nine unities, the inner display of vacuous function—quiescent and vast, the primal abode—thus manifests as the rare. Vast and unobstructed, it appears as the level; wondrous eloquence without limit responds as the subtle. All-embracing without beyond, universally complete as emptiness; receiving and containing all things, universally pervading as the cavernous; unbounded and unobstructed, it responds as the wondrous non-being.

From this wondrous non-being, responsive teachings gradually manifest, first revealing the spirit of intent, then establishing the spirit of will, and further the spirit of thought. The three thoughts trace their origin, and responsive teachings arise in function. Thus from orthodox wisdom arises true wisdom, and from true wisdom arises expedient wisdom. From this expedient wisdom, the Three Treasures are revealed: essence, spirit, and qi.

Essence is governed by numinous wisdom; spirit, unfathomable, operates through transformation; qi, as configuration, functions through generation. Though their functions differ, they are called the Three, yet their substance is indivisible, hence named the Three-in-One. Within this Three-in-One, three bodies are further revealed: first, the body of form and mind; second, the body of the Three Caverns; third, the body of wondrous virtue.

The body of form and mind: the fundamental body of the quiescent earth, with the True Unity’s wondrous wisdom as its essence. The body of the Three Caverns: the stages of cultivation and ascent, establishing the origin in accord with rank, verifying fruition and ascending position, universally delivering all beings—this is great wisdom. Originally, form is a fetter, obstructing the stages of ascent. From the nine sages downward, all seek advancement in rank; bound by the fetters of desire, they are collectively called possessors of form. When the fetters of the true Dao are exhausted, only the wondrous mind remains.

Those who verify the Dao-fruit possess all virtues; quiescent and invisible, they are called wondrous non-being. When active, they respond and welcome, sharing substance with things, though mind and form are wondrous, they become visible—hence named wondrous being. Through position, retribution is felt; form congeals, ascending the mysterious. Advancing to become an exalted sage, attaining the supreme sagely fruit, forgetting cause and forgetting effect, naturally aligning with true nature, merging with the great Dao, blending indistinguishably with things—none surpass the exalted, thus first called the Heavenly Venerable.

Therefore, from the Heavenly Venerable, responsive bodies gradually manifest, generating realms. The primal qi of the Mysterious Origin universally pervades the radiance of the body; the three qi transform form, unfolding the Three Caverns. The Origin emits blue radiance, ascending to generate heaven; the Primal emits white radiance, arising in the midst to generate humanity; the Mysterious emits yellow radiance, descending to generate earth. From these three colors, the Heavenly Venerable of the Primal Origin generates ninefold radiance, universally emanating the Dharma-body, its luminosity pervasively illuminating.

First generated from chaos, chaos as dark blue radiance;
Chaos generates the cavernous, the cavernous as red radiance;
The cavernous generates the vast, the vast as blue radiance;
The Primal generates the luminous, the luminous as green radiance;
The luminous generates the bright, the bright as yellow radiance;
The bright generates the fleeing, the fleeing as white radiance;
The Mysterious generates the harmonious, the harmonious as purple radiance;
The harmonious generates the flaming, the flaming as azure radiance;
The flaming generates the flowing, the flowing as black radiance.
The ninefold radiance shines brilliantly, suffusing the Dharma-body.

From this ninefold radiance, realms universally arise: above, generating the three realms and thirty-six heavens, manifesting the celestial countenance, vacuously and cavernously luminous; below, generating the three realms and thirty-six emperors, provisionally manifesting responsive bodies, benevolently bestowing the gate of life, gradually and suddenly guiding to tranquility—hence named the Three Caverns and thirty-six marks.

*Upper Clarity’s Most High Scripture of the Heavenly Dragon’s Ascent, Scroll Three*
*The Heavenly Venerable’s Dharma-body Generates the Three Realms and Thirty-six Marks, Chapter Six: The Primal Establishment*

Lord Ning addressed the Yellow Emperor, saying: "Formerly, I received from the Heavenly Venerable on the Great Brahma Heaven the *Scripture of the Primal Establishment of the Heavenly Venerable’s Responsive Generation of Marks*, wherein responsive bodies generate marks, and realms project form. Above, they become the Three Clarities and thirty-six Heavenly Venerables; below, they generate the three realms and thirty-six Heavenly Emperors, thus manifesting the seventy-two marks universally pervading the mundane and sagely.

The retribution of humans and heavens differs. Within the Three Clarities’ upper realms, wondrous quiescence is constant; the nine grades of the mysterious ascent forget merit and verify retribution. Within the three realms, there are beings of perception, deluded thoughts congealing firmly, clinging and indulging. Therefore, thirty-two heavens of responsive interaction are established, provisionally containing yin and yang, universally generating and embracing. The primal qi of the Mysterious Origin, the eight luminaries perfectly radiant, above become the four Brahma heavens at the summit of the three realms.

The Heavenly Venerable, in successive kalpas, unfolds generation, below forming the three realms. Above and below interpenetrate, the thirty-two Heavenly Emperors collectively govern the four eights. The great image interweaves, the nine qi mutually interpenetrate, forming the revolving kalpa. The thirty-two Emperors laterally traverse the celestial pivot, each constituting one heaven of the twenty-eight constellations. The nine heavens layer upon one another, also corresponding to the eight directions and nine palaces of the earth. The heavens of the Four Heavenly Kings interpenetrate above and below, also corresponding to the four directions and four eights of life’s lords. All receive the nine qi, the two halves harmonizing. Origin and trace merge, pervading the thirty-six positions—hence the thirty-six Emperors interpenetrate above and below.

Heaven descends one qi, and the five qi are generated, provisionally containing yin and yang, harmonizing qi to form bodies. Thus yang has lesser yang and greater yang, while yin has lesser yin and greater yin."

Next is revealed the fifth *Mysterious Immortal Verification Grade*, establishing the *Mysterious Brahmā Contemplative Wisdom Heaven*. Next is revealed the sixth *Perfected Immortal Verification Grade*, establishing the *Cloud Brahmā Ātāna Heaven*.

Furthermore, the ninth: *Yan* is born from *Yan*, and *Yan* becomes black light. Without relying on sun or moon, it is naturally luminous, demonstrating non-thought and non-desire. It severs the bonds of the womb and eliminates attachment to form, attaining a mind of non-thought and karma without fetters. Those who attain the ultimate fruit ascend to this heaven, hence it is called the *Non-Thought, Non-Fetter, Non-Attachment Heaven*. Its heavenly sovereign is the *Supreme Perfected Jade Emperor*, who expounds the five desires and the illusory emptiness of thoughts and imaginings.

Thus is revealed the seventh *Heavenly Immortal Verification Grade*, establishing the *Cavernous Subtle Containing Heaven*. Next is revealed the eighth *Spiritual Immortal Verification Grade*, establishing the *Mysterious Upper Extinction-Nothingness Heaven*. Next is revealed the ninth *Ultimate Immortal Verification Grade*, establishing the *Utmost Form Ruo Na Heaven*.

The ninefold unity corresponds to the body, manifesting the *Response Body*. The three caverns interpenetrate form, unfolding the thirty-six sections, responding to the three realms and thirty-six heavens. From non-being to being, gradually entrusted to language, yet not abiding in being—its nature is unimpeded. This is called the *Response Body’s Thirty-Six Aspects*.

---

*The Highest Clarity Scripture of the Celestial Dragon’s Ascent*, Scroll Four
*The Heavenly Worthy’s Response and Descent: The Primordial Establishment of the Three Realms and Thirty-Six Aspects*, Chapter Nine

Lord Ning addressed the Yellow Emperor, saying: In the ancient *Dragon Han* kalpa, the *Primordial Beginning* unfolded the chart. Without form or name, the *Heavenly Worthy* in the *Great Veil Heaven* above generated the *Three Clarities* and thirty-six heavens, and below generated the *Three Realms* and thirty-six emperors. His body emitted five-colored *Response Transformation Body* lights, and for the various heavenly emperors, he expounded the *Scripture of the Primordial Establishment of the Heavenly Origin*.

First were established the *Four Brahmā Northern Perfected Upper Heavens*, serving as the *Eastern Florescence*, *Western Numinous*, and *Southern Ultimate*. The four heavens were layered, their four threads interwoven, each generating eight luminous scenes. Four times eight interflow, thus forming the four times eight thirty-two heavens. Internally containing the four *Brahmā* and thirty-six aspects, responding to the ten titles, they entrust their traces to the various heavens:

1. *Self-So*, the root of all things;
2. *Without Limit*, unfathomable in its depth;
3. *Great Dao*, universally embracing and nurturing;
4. *Utmost Perfected*, true and utterly pure;
5. *Supreme*, utmost in greatness and height;
6. *Venerable Lord*, responding across the ages;
7. *Lofty Emperor*, radiant and supremely exalted;
8. *Heavenly Worthy*, the honored one among heavens;
9. *Jade Emperor*, the noble and honored lord of jade;
10. *Your Majesty*, the supreme lord of all heavens.

None is higher above; among heavens, none is more honored. The title *Your Majesty* admits no surpassing. Seventy-two aspects illuminate above and below; eighty-one excellences radiate boundlessly. Above, there are no four emperors; below, the four directions are complete. The four *Brahmā* interflow to generate, establishing four threads. Four heavens, each with eight gates, totaling thirty-two. Combining the central four nines yields thirty-six grades.

Thus, the wondrous *qi* of the *Upper Three Clarities* and nine heavens descends to generate the *Three Realms*. The nine [missing character] respond to generation. From the first above, the *Yūdāna Immeasurable First Upper Heaven*, born from *Hun*, *Hun* as azure hue, above it coalesce the four *Brahmā* and *Great Clarity* heavens. Next are born the four persons, generating twenty-two thousand two hundred *qi*, forming the *Great Ultimate Level Nurturing Jia Yi Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for one trillion nine hundred thirty-two billion seven hundred thirty-five million two hundred eighty thousand three hundred twenty million years. Advancing in immortal grades, next is the second *Supreme Meditative Goodness Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Hun* born from *Dong*, *Dong* as crimson light. Above it generate thirty-three thousand *qi*, forming the *Dragon Transformation Brahmā Crossing Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for nine hundred sixty-six billion three hundred sixty-seven million six hundred forty-one thousand six hundred million years. Advancing in immortal grades, next is the third *Brahmā Supervisor Xu Yan Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Dong* born from *Hao*, *Hao* as blue-green hue. Above it generate forty-four thousand *qi*, forming the *Great Release Jade Dragon Ascendant Victory Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for four hundred eighty-three billion one hundred eighty-three million eight hundred twenty billion eight hundred million years. Advancing in immortal grades, next is the fourth *Tranquil Dou Shu Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Hao* born from *Hao*, *Hao* as green hue. Above it generate fifty-five thousand *qi*, forming the *Great Void Utmost Constant Fusion Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for two hundred forty-one billion five hundred ninety-one million one hundred ninety-one billion forty million years. Advancing in immortal grades, these four heavens’ people delight in stillness and joy.

Next is the fifth *Pāramitā Non-Arrogant Joy Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Hao* born from *Jing*, *Jing* as yellow hue. Above it generate sixty-six thousand *qi*, forming the *Great Simplicity Elegant Joy Forbidden Upper Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for one hundred twenty billion seven hundred ninety-five million five hundred ninety-five billion five thousand three hundred million years. The people of this heaven, their *qi*-contemplation increasingly wondrous, cultivate the four equalities, gradually eliminating residual habits, ascending to the *Four Peoples’ Heaven*.

Next is the sixth *Cavern Origin Transformative Responsive Sound Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Jing* born from *Dun*, *Dun* as white hue. Above it generate seventy-seven thousand *qi*, forming the *Great Literature Glorious Wondrous Accomplishment Heaven*. The people of this heaven live for sixty billion three hundred ninety-seven million seven hundred ninety-seven billion seven thousand six hundred million years. In this heaven, fearing total loss, they contemplate this consciousness—whether existent or non-existent—thus ascending to the *Great Simplicity Elegant Joy Forbidden Upper Heaven*.

Next is the seventh *Numinous Transformation Brahmā Assistant Heaven*. From this heaven, *qi* gradually flows downward, *Dun* born from *Rong*, *Rong* as purple hue. Above it generate eighty-eight thousand *qi*, forming the *Abyssal Penetration Primordial Cavern Heaven*.
